			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>What We Do</strong><br />
Based in Chicago, we own and operate a suite of digital healthcare information networks delivering condition-specific video programming at point-of-care in all 50 states. We empower healthcare professionals to engage patients while curating content personalized for each member practice. As a mission-driven organization, we strive to deliver media as a service to educate and inspire audiences utilizing the latest digital media technologies. For more information, please see www.contextmediainc.com.</p>
<p>
<strong>Who We Are</strong><br />
Working at ContextMedia is an entrepreneurial adventure with high expectations, agile plans and a fun environment. We are creative, problem-solvers and fight until we win; but above all measure our success by the service we provide to healthcare professionals, patients, and industry to improve health outcomes.</p>
<p>
<strong>What We Need</strong><br />
The Member Outreach Executive will be responsible for selling ContextMedia&#39;s platforms to physician practices and hospitals nationwide predominantly through phone sales. You will provide insight and understanding into prospect decision-making, questions and concerns. Candidates must be able to explain the benefits of our products and services with a values-&shy;‚Äêbased sales approach. To do this you must develop a deep understanding of the company and its business model, as well as its networks&rsquo; features, benefits and principles in order to communicate these to members. The position will also require attending industry conferences and events, traveling for sales meetings, and participating in networking events. You cannot be scared to pick up a phone and/or introduce yourself in network settings.</p>
<p>
<strong>Who We Need</strong><br />
An intelligent, hard-working, and detail-oriented individual who has two or more years of sales experience. This individual should have an understanding of a sales process. We need individuals who have the natural ability to build relationships over short periods of time by being clear with concise usage of words to engage and excite prospective members on the phone. To be blunt, we need go-getters who take pride in their sales but are open to learning and growing over time.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br />
<br />
<strong>What You Need</strong><br />
Must possess a lot of positive energy, self-initiative and a can-do attitude! Prior experience working in a fast-paced environment, managing multiple deadlines and interfacing with a diverse group of team members. You need to be comfortable being on the phone for several hours each day. Strong communication skills required, both verbal and written. This is an evolving sale, you must able to adjust your sale on the fly and not be set in your own sales ways. You need to be able to work within a team dynamic, if you like to work alone in a quiet environment, this is not the roll for you.</p>
<p>
<strong>How To Apply</strong><br />
Please submit a resume and cover letter at www.contextmediainc.com/careers. <u>Please address in the cover letter why you&#39;d like to be a part of the ContextMedia family and how your skills are well suited for this position</u>.</p>
