An Executive Assistant to provide full and diversified administrative support to the Chief Executive Officer. This person will use broad and comprehensive experience, skills, and knowledge in organizational procedures and practices, and serve as a facilitator and doer to coordinate deadlines, obtain requested information, maintain reports, and other related activities. In other words, you know how to get things done! Responsibilities will include managing incoming calls, daily calendars, scheduling of appointments, meetings, and conference calls, assisting with presentations, frequent travel arrangement, and the ability to assist in special projects.<br />
