<br />
<strong>What You Need</strong><br />
Must possess a proactive work ethic, a flexible, team-oriented attitude, and ability to work independently, typically managing different and conflicting objectives and projects all at one time. The Executive Assistant will have client contact and will be exposed to sensitive information, and thus must use considerable tact, diplomacy, and judgment. Must be proficient in MS Word, Excel, and PowerPoint. The EA will need to be responsive outside of regular business hours and be accessible evenings and weekends. Minimum of 5 years of comparable work experience and Bachelor&rsquo;s degree required.<br />
