<strong>What We Do</strong><br />
Based in Chicago, we own and operate a suite of digital healthcare information networks delivering condition-specific video programming at point-of-care in all 50 states. We empower healthcare professionals to engage patients while curating content personalized for each member practice. As a mission-driven organization, we strive to deliver media as a service to educate and inspire audiences utilizing the latest digital media technologies. For more information, please see www.contextmediainc.com.<br />
<br />
<strong>Who We Are</strong><br />
Working at ContextMedia is an entrepreneurial adventure with high expectations, agile plans and a fun environment. We are creative, problem-solvers and fight until we win; but above all measure our success by the service we provide to healthcare professionals, patients, and industry to improve health outcomes.</p>
<p>
<strong>What We Need</strong><br />
The Finance Manager will be responsible for all financial accounting and reporting functions including: general ledger maintenance; month end closes; preparation and distribution of monthly financial statements; expense tracking and analysis; budgeting &amp; forecasting and external reporting. This individual will also be responsible for developing, measuring and analyzing key operating and financial performance indicators. Our Finance Manager will work directly with the senior management team on strategic planning, evaluation and analysis of business opportunities and financial presentations.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Who We Need</strong><br />
A self motivated, high energy, detail oriented individual who can continuously and effectively manage multiple assignments and projects.&nbsp; The role will entail frequent communication with operating teams and stakeholders, requiring excellent communication skills. Our successful Finance Manager must be highly analytical, extremely organized, and have the ability to deliver reports/projects in an accurate and timely manner. You&rsquo;ll be required to develop, maintain and distribute ad-hoc reports and financial models as needed, and be asked to evaluate and provide recommendations on policies, procedures and financial/accounting matters.<br />
<br />
<strong>What You Need</strong><br />
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Accounting/Finance. A minimum of three years public accounting or experience in financial reporting and analysis. CPA is a plus. The Finance Manager must demonstrate that he/she can thrive in a fast paced, dynamic environment.&nbsp; This position will interface frequently with members of senior management and operating team leads. You&rsquo;ll need the ability to provide and present accurate data/information while working collaboratively with the rest of the organization. The position will require a solid work ethic and willingness to put in long hours when required.</p>
<p>
<strong>How To Apply</strong><br />
Please submit a resume and cover letter at www.contextmediainc.com/careers. <u>Please address in the cover letter why you&#39;d like to be a part of the ContextMedia family and how your skills are well suited for this position</u>.</p>
