			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>What We Do</strong><br />
Based in Chicago, we own and operate a suite of digital healthcare information networks delivering condition-specific video programming at point-of-care in all 50 states. We empower healthcare professionals to engage patients while curating content personalized for each member practice. As a mission-driven organization, we strive to deliver media as a service to educate and inspire audiences utilizing the latest digital media technologies. For more information, please see www.contextmediainc.com.</p>
<p>
<strong>Who We Are</strong><br />
Working at ContextMedia is an entrepreneurial adventure with high expectations, agile plans and a fun environment. We are creative, problem-solvers and fight until we win; but above all measure our success by the service we provide to healthcare professionals, patients, and industry to improve health outcomes.</p>
<p>
<strong>What We Need</strong><br />
We need an energetic and passionate individual who will own the responsibility of expanding the ContextMedia family by bringing on talent in roles such as network operations, account management, sales and finance. As a fast-growth organization, we are always seeking talent but take the care to truly add team members for the long haul, not a number to put sales on the board. The Talent Scout will be responsible for the entire recruiting process, from sourcing, vetting, interviewing to on-boarding. In addition to this, the person will take ownership of employee development through lunch &#39;n&#39; learns, fun team activities and maintaining our initiatives such as Book Club and Wii competitions. Finally, this person will fulfill administrative duties such as benefits and performance evaluations.</p>
<p>
<strong>Who We Need</strong><br />
A person who thrives on building relationships and developing networks, internally with our team as well as externally with our community. This individual must be passionate, driven, intelligent, creative, and a fighter! They need to embody the paradox of our culture, which is being detail-oriented while seeing the big picture, being data-driven while being highly personable, being a team player while taking individual ownership, being very focused about work and being a fun companion to support a team-member&#39;s band at a fundraiser!</p>
<p>
<strong>What You Need</strong><br />
Experience recruiting for high-growth firms that focus on building the right team based on culture. The Talent Scout will often participate in networking activities and industry conferences to source candidates, so should be available evenings and weekends occasionally. The right attitude, aspiration and work ethic is a requirement. This position will be collaborating with the entire organization and working closely with the founders and senior managers.</p>
<p>
<strong>How To Apply</strong><br />
Please submit a resume and cover letter at www.contextmediainc.com/careers. <u>Please address in the cover letter why you&#39;d like to be a part of the ContextMedia family and how your skills are well suited for this position.</u></p>
